<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>API Overview on notd</title><link>/docs/overview/</link><description>Recent content in API Overview on notd</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="/docs/overview/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Core Concepts</title><link>/docs/overview/core-concepts/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/docs/overview/core-concepts/</guid><description>&lt;h3 id="pages">Pages&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Pages are top-level containers for notes. Each page has a unique name and can contain multiple notes.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="notes">Notes&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Notes are the core content blocks that belong to pages. Notes can be nested under other notes, creating a hierarchical structure.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="properties">Properties&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Properties are metadata extracted from content using pattern matching:&lt;/p>
&lt;ul>
&lt;li>&lt;code>{key::value}&lt;/code> - Public property (weight 2)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>{key:::value}&lt;/code> - Internal property (weight 3)&lt;/li>
&lt;li>&lt;code>{key::::value}&lt;/code> - System log property (weight 4)&lt;/li>
&lt;/ul>
&lt;h3 id="task-states">Task States&lt;/h3>
